TI  - Capital Budgeting frameworks for the Multinational Corporation
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 113
EP  - 123
VL  - 13
IS  - 2
AB  - This article discusses the relative merits of different capital budgeting techniques used by MNCs. The purpose is to show that the APV method, which has recently gained popularity, can cause incorrect choices to be made between competing projects unless the NPV is already determined. The author suggests that complicated cost of capital adjustments may be the only route to calculating a project's NPV correctly.
